  <bioghist audience="internal" id="aspace_342e978013afb8aaad060174897de517">
    <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
<p>Alan Hedge received his B.S., M.S. and Ph.D. degrees from the University of Sheffield. His research and teaching focus on issues of design and workplace ergonomics as these affect the health, comfort and productivity of workers. He is Professor Emeritus in the Dept. of Design and Environmental Analysis, Cornell University.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_80255adfd474e85a338801197609221e">
    <head>Scope and content</head>
<p>Includes office environment survey results for individual buildings, including slides.</p>  </scopecontent>
